the dinner crowds?

39:10.974 --> 39:14.268
- Who is this young woman...
- This is Polly Prince.

39:14.352 --> 39:17.604
Polly, these are my parents,
Irving and Vivian Feffer.

39:17.689 --> 39:20.441
- It's so good meeting you.
- How are you?

39:20.525 --> 39:23.402
I can't believe you're
eating Indian. You hate spicy food.

39:23.486 --> 39:24.945
No, I don't.

39:25.864 --> 39:28.615
Well, I'm going to... Psst!
I'm going to ask...

39:28.825 --> 39:31.201
I'm going to ask
this nice Native American man

39:31.286 --> 39:32.411
to get us a bigger table.

39:32.495 --> 39:34.872
They're Indian.
You can call them Indian. It's okay.

39:34.956 --> 39:39.752
Hi. Need big table, please.
Four people. Many thanks.

39:42.505 --> 39:43.672
Okay.

39:44.591 --> 39:46.842
Now, how do you kids
know each other?

39:46.926 --> 39:50.846
We went to middle school together.
We were both in the Model UN.

39:50.930 --> 39:53.432
You still work in government, honey?

39:53.516 --> 39:56.185
No. I'm a waitress.

39:57.645 --> 39:59.521
She's also writing
a children's book.

39:59.606 --> 40:01.315
Oh, very nice.

40:02.067 --> 40:04.401
