56:40.064 --> 56:41.981
Dirty? Why are their hands dirty??

56:42.066 --> 56:43.775
Only one out of six people

56:43.859 --> 56:45.693
wash hands
when they go to the bathroom.

56:45.778 --> 56:48.362
When you think you're innocently
eating a bar snack,

56:48.447 --> 56:50.573
you're ingesting
potentially deadly bacteria

56:50.657 --> 56:52.742
from 39 soil-handed strangers.

56:52.826 --> 56:55.036
People wonder why
they get E. Coli poisoning

56:55.120 --> 56:56.454
or salmonella or hepatitis.

56:56.538 --> 57:00.041
They should look at the snack bowl
at their local watering hole.

57:01.418 --> 57:04.879
I'm not being neurotic.
It's a hot zone in there.

57:09.510 --> 57:11.552
How could you have eaten those?

57:11.678 --> 57:14.263
I made such a compelling argument.

57:14.348 --> 57:16.682
I like to live life on the edge.

57:17.267 --> 57:19.852
- Thank you.
- Yeah, you never know.

57:32.199 --> 57:33.908
You don't have to do this.

57:34.034 --> 57:36.869
I don't care that you don't know
how to dance!

57:36.954 --> 57:39.539
I thought I'd give it one last try.
Hey, Javi.

57:39.623 --> 57:41.624
Hey, Reuben. You ready?

57:41.708 --> 57:42.834
Uh-huh.

57:42.918 --> 57:44.043
What's happening?

57:44.128 --> 57:45.920
- IFuerte!
- What?

57:48.715 --> 57:50.216
What are you doing?

59:11.048 --> 59:13.507
I don't know where that came from!

59:13.634 --> 59:15.301
It was just awesome.

59:16.303 --> 59:17.470
Holy shit.

59:25.145 --> 59:27.230
What are you doing here?

59:30.234 --> 59:31.567
I'm back.

59:34.196 --> 59:35.613
Who's this?

59:36.323 --> 59:38.783
- Who's this? This is my girlfriend.
- What?

59:38.867 --> 59:41.118
- You have a girlfriend?
- I'm not your girlfriend.

59:41.203 --> 59:44.497
I mean, we're just, kind of...
Hi, I'm Polly.

59:46.333 --> 59:48.167
- Lisa.
- Right.

59:55.968 --> 01:00:00.346
You guys probably have a lot
to talk about, so I'll just go.

01:00:00.430 --> 01:00:03.266
- I don't want you to go.
- Please, I want to go. Bye, Lisa.

01:00:03.350 --> 01:00:05.309
- Nice to meet you.
- I don't want you to go.

01:00:05.394 --> 01:00:07.478
You got to talk about it.

01:00:08.272 --> 01:00:09.855
I'm just going to go.

01:00:16.697 --> 01:00:17.780
I don't understand.

01:00:17.864 --> 01:00:20.658
I thought you were really happy
with Claude.

01:00:20.742 --> 01:00:24.704
I was, for a few weeks, but all he
talked about was scuba diving.

01:00:24.788 --> 01:00:27.164
- Really?
- I missed you, Reuben.

01:00:27.249 --> 01:00:30.584
I missed you, too, but come on!
What was I supposed to do?

01:00:30.669 --> 01:00:32.962
I moved on. I'm in a relationship.

01:00:33.046 --> 01:00:34.630
- What, with that Polly person?
- Yeah.

01:00:34.715 --> 01:00:36.632
She doesn't call herself
your girlfriend.

01:00:36.717 --> 01:00:39.468
That's... No, she just doesn't like
the phrasing.

01:00:39.553 --> 01:00:42.138
Okay, then,
let me just ask you this.

01:00:42.222 --> 01:00:46.225
Are you really going to spend
the rest of your life with her?

01:00:46.727 --> 01:00:48.311
I don't know, Lisa.

01:00:48.645 --> 01:00:51.355
Because I'm ready to do that
with you.

01:00:51.481 --> 01:00:54.233
I made a mistake,
and I took you for granted.

01:00:54.401 --> 01:00:58.404
But I promise you that I will
never, ever hurt you again.

01:01:00.866 --> 01:01:02.867
I love you, Reuben.

01:01:09.833 --> 01:01:11.417
You know what?

01:01:12.085 --> 01:01:15.629
I think you should
go stay with your parents. Okay?

01:01:15.714 --> 01:01:18.507
- I've to leave in a week.
- What? Where are you going?

01:01:18.592 --> 01:01:21.802
I'm going into the house
I bought for us. Remember?

01:01:21.887 --> 01:01:24.847
Let's do it together.
Let's go move into our house.

01:01:24.931 --> 01:01:28.476
We don't just...
No. We can't just go... I can't...

01:01:31.897 --> 01:01:34.982
I don't even know
what to say right now, okay? So...

01:01:38.320 --> 01:01:39.487
Okay.

01:01:42.991 --> 01:01:45.076
If you want to get back together
with her...

01:01:45.160 --> 01:01:48.120
No, I wouldn't be seeing you
if I was planning...

01:01:48.205 --> 01:01:51.415
It's cool. You guys are married.
She came back.

01:01:52.084 --> 01:01:54.377
How's it coming
with Herb Lazare, D.D. S?

01:01:54.795 --> 01:01:57.588
I haven't even gotten to it.
I'm still working on Van Lew.

01:01:57.672 --> 01:02:00.299
I thought you decided on Van Lew
two weeks ago.

01:02:00.384 --> 01:02:02.635
We present to AFLAC on Wednesday.

01:02:02.719 --> 01:02:05.179
- Can you hang on? Hang on.
- I have to go.

01:02:05.263 --> 01:02:08.057
- Better not be bonus-hunting on me.
Bonus-hunting?

01:02:08.141 --> 01:02:11.560
That man's career's on the line.
I owe him a thorough analysis.

01:02:11.645 --> 01:02:12.770
All right.

01:02:12.979 --> 01:02:15.523
I'm going to Barbados with
my mistress for the weekend.

01:02:15.607 --> 01:02:18.317
I want this Van Lew thing settled
by the time I get back.

01:02:18.402 --> 01:02:20.653
I am on it, and I'll make it happen.

01:02:20.779 --> 01:02:22.238
Good things.

01:02:24.157 --> 01:02:25.241
Damn!

01:02:26.660 --> 01:02:28.077
- Hey, pal.
- Hey, Larry.

01:02:28.161 --> 01:02:30.162
Lisa dropped this off for you.

01:02:30.831 --> 01:02:32.081
Oh!

01:02:32.916 --> 01:02:34.041
Thanks.

01:02:45.303 --> 01:02:49.932
I met Lisa Kramer, who showed me
an apartment, which I rented...

01:02:50.016 --> 01:02:52.726
- just so she'd go out with me.
- I gave him a good price.

01:02:52.811 --> 01:02:54.895
Not good enough. She's a killer.

01:03:06.283 --> 01:03:08.159
I just can't believe she came back.

01:03:08.243 --> 01:03:11.620
Can we just focus for a second?
I'm almost finished.

01:03:11.705 --> 01:03:14.748
- What's next?
- Polly's career prospects.

01:03:14.833 --> 01:03:17.877
Risky. She's writing a children's
book where kids get maimed.

01:03:17.961 --> 01:03:22.173
Her lack of career is a positive.
She'd have more time for the kids.

01:03:22.466 --> 01:03:26.385
You're skewing the numbers in
her favor. Why are we doing this?

01:03:26.470 --> 01:03:28.387
Because I'm confused.

01:03:28.472 --> 01:03:30.014
My goddamn wife

01:03:30.098 --> 01:03:32.766
shows up on my doorstep
wanting to get back together.

01:03:32.851 --> 01:03:34.727
Polly's freaking out.

01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:37.938
I just want to make sure
I'm making the right decision.

01:03:39.357 --> 01:03:42.109
I don't see how putting these
two girls in the Riskmaster

01:03:42.194 --> 01:03:44.236
will help you make up your mind.

01:03:48.867 --> 01:03:50.784
- Interesting.
- What's it say?

01:03:51.453 --> 01:03:52.495
Polly!

01:03:53.121 --> 01:03:54.663
- Polly?
- Yeah.

01:03:54.873 --> 01:03:57.958
No way. Just cut your losses
and get back with Lisa.

01:03:58.043 --> 01:04:01.212
I checked it three times.
It says she's the safer choice.

01:04:01.296 --> 01:04:02.630
Whatever.

01:04:03.924 --> 01:04:07.551
By the way, is your health okay?
You're looking thin.

01:04:07.636 --> 01:04:09.845
Polly's been making me
eat ethnic food,

01:04:09.930 --> 01:04:12.348
so I've been throwing up
a lot lately.

01:04:12.807 --> 01:04:13.933
Cool.

01:04:14.017 --> 01:04:15.351
Polly Prince.

01:04:17.270 --> 01:04:18.812
Polly Feffer.

01:04:21.316 --> 01:04:23.234
Polly Prince-Feffer.

01:04:23.652 --> 01:04:26.320
You can't cancel.
You were so excited to go.

01:04:26.488 --> 01:04:27.696
I know, but...

01:04:27.781 --> 01:04:31.033
We fell in love
with these funny Bolivian mud huts.

01:04:31.117 --> 01:04:32.826
- Hold on.
- So we had our designer

01:04:32.911 --> 01:04:35.079
use a similar color palette
in here.

01:04:35.163 --> 01:04:38.999
Hi. I'm sorry, I'm on the phone.
Would you just please keep it...

01:04:40.669 --> 01:04:43.963
Also, I feel weird going away
for the weekend

01:04:44.047 --> 01:04:47.466
- when your wife just came back.
- You're making this such a big deal.

01:04:47.551 --> 01:04:50.469
I told you, I'm not getting back
together with her.

01:04:51.846 --> 01:04:53.347
- So are you coming?
- I'm coming.

01:04:53.848 --> 01:04:55.432
- All right.
- Okay?

01:04:55.809 --> 01:04:56.850
Bye.

01:05:21.751 --> 01:05:25.296
- You're good. You're a natural.
- This is amazing!

01:05:25.547 --> 01:05:28.632
Hey, Leland, are those storm clouds
up ahead?

01:05:30.260 --> 01:05:34.305
No, we might get a light dusting.
Nothing to write home about.

01:05:38.602 --> 01:05:40.019
Are you sure you're all right?

01:05:40.103 --> 01:05:43.063
I'm okay. I don't think I have
my sea legs yet.

01:05:43.148 --> 01:05:45.316
- I'll be out in a sec.
- All right.

01:05:45.942 --> 01:05:47.234
Oh, God.

01:05:52.949 --> 01:05:56.327
I know we haven't been seeing each
other long, but I feel like...

01:05:56.411 --> 01:05:58.787
it's time we take things
to the next level

01:05:58.872 --> 01:06:02.291
and I'd like you
to consider moving in with me.

01:06:11.051 --> 01:06:13.177
Why don't we just move in together?

01:06:21.186 --> 01:06:24.021
Oh, yeah, we're going to have
ourselves a tussle.

01:06:26.816 --> 01:06:30.736
Rodolfo's in your toiletry kit.
Did you know that?

01:06:31.029 --> 01:06:33.155
Did you pack him, or did you...

01:06:33.239 --> 01:06:34.573
What is this?

01:06:34.658 --> 01:06:38.077
Why am I in your computer
on your Riskmaster thingy?

01:06:38.161 --> 01:06:40.162
Okay, you know what?
I can explain this.

01:06:40.246 --> 01:06:42.998
It's fascinating, actually.
I learned a lot about myself.

01:06:43.083 --> 01:06:46.960
I've learned that I have no career,
I'm flaky, I like ethnic food.

01:06:47.045 --> 01:06:48.712
Would you let me explain?

01:06:48.797 --> 01:06:52.091
Lisa came back, and I've been trying
to figure things out.

01:06:52.175 --> 01:06:56.095
- What are you figuring out?
- Just about us, and our future.

01:06:56.638 --> 01:06:59.682
Future? What are you talking about?
What future?

01:06:59.766 --> 01:07:02.685
Reuben, come on.
This is a fling, you know?

01:07:02.769 --> 01:07:05.229
What, did you think
we'd get married?

01:07:05.313 --> 01:07:06.772
Whoa! Maybe.

01:07:07.649 --> 01:07:09.692
I was gonna ask you
to move in with me first.

01:07:09.776 --> 01:07:13.320
You expect me to move to the
suburbs with you? Are you insane?

01:07:13.947 --> 01:07:16.281
Why is that so crazy?
People do that all the time.

01:07:16.366 --> 01:07:20.202
They have kids, they make plans,
they get married, they buy houses.

01:07:20.286 --> 01:07:22.204
That's you, Reuben. You do that.

01:07:22.288 --> 01:07:24.790
That's what you do.
I don't live my life that way.

01:07:24.874 --> 01:07:27.501
Is your lack of a plan
that different than my plan?

01:07:27.585 --> 01:07:30.796
- I don't have a plan.
- You're on the non-plan plan.

01:07:30.880 --> 01:07:34.007
- I am not on a non-plan plan.
- You are, too.

01:07:34.092 --> 01:07:36.593
I've never met anybody
more afraid of commitment.

01:07:36.678 --> 01:07:39.930
You were a senior delegate
at the Model UN, Polly.

01:07:40.014 --> 01:07:41.765
What the hell happened to you?

01:07:46.312 --> 01:07:49.356
Come on, you mother!
You can do better than that!

01:07:49.566 --> 01:07:51.442
I've been living my life, okay?

01:07:51.526 --> 01:07:54.403
I've been in good relationships
and in shitty ones.

01:07:54.487 --> 01:07:58.031
And I've moved a lot
and I've been happy and sad

01:07:58.116 --> 01:08:00.159
and lonely and that's what
I've been doing.

01:08:00.243 --> 01:08:02.453
Which is more than I can say
for some freak

01:08:02.537 --> 01:08:05.873
who thinks he'll get Ebola virus
from a bowl of mixed nuts.

01:08:05.999 --> 01:08:08.584
Those nuts have pee on them!
It's common sense.

01:08:08.668 --> 01:08:11.837
Trust me, that is so far
beyond common sense.

01:08:14.716 --> 01:08:16.550
You don't understand
what I grew up with.

01:08:16.634 --> 01:08:18.301
My mother made me
afraid of everything.

01:08:18.386 --> 01:08:21.721
Big deal, Reuben.
My dad had a whole second family.

01:08:21.805 --> 01:08:24.057
- What?
- Yeah, on Long Island.

01:08:24.142 --> 01:08:27.310
A wife and kids
and a golden retriever.

01:08:27.520 --> 01:08:29.188
A second family?

01:08:30.148 --> 01:08:32.483
Whatever. Hey, you know what?

01:08:34.527 --> 01:08:36.569
I'm glad I saw that. I am.

01:08:36.654 --> 01:08:40.783
Because I'm going to make this
really easy for you, Reuben.

01:08:40.867 --> 01:08:43.743
I have no interest...

01:08:43.870 --> 01:08:47.331
in getting married
and moving to the suburbs.

01:08:47.415 --> 01:08:50.000
And obviously that's
really important to you.

01:08:50.084 --> 01:08:52.544
So here's what I think
your new plan should be.

01:08:52.629 --> 01:08:56.131
You should get back together
with Lisa, move into your house

01:08:56.216 --> 01:08:57.841
and move on with your life.

01:08:57.926 --> 01:09:01.220
And I think you guys
will be really happy together.

01:09:01.805 --> 01:09:03.013
Oh, dear Lord.

01:09:09.645 --> 01:09:11.939
You're not making my job
any easier, Leland.

01:09:12.023 --> 01:09:15.526
Come on, Reub.
Weather report said sunny skies.

01:09:47.517 --> 01:09:49.393
Hey, it's Polly Prince.

01:09:49.519 --> 01:09:52.979
Leave me a message,
or call back, or not.

01:09:53.064 --> 01:09:55.065
You know, whatever. Okay, bye.

01:09:55.149 --> 01:09:57.609
Hey, Polly, it's me. Listen...

01:09:58.069 --> 01:10:01.697
I'd like to talk to you, because I
feel bad about what happened.

01:10:02.532 --> 01:10:04.074
Give me a call on my cell phone.

01:10:18.381 --> 01:10:20.632
- Hello?
- Hi. It's Lisa.

01:10:23.344 --> 01:10:25.178
So, how's the house?

01:10:25.847 --> 01:10:27.848
The house is great.

01:10:29.058 --> 01:10:31.059
It's big, but, you know, great.

01:10:31.269 --> 01:10:34.730
I can't wait to see it.
Did you get the gift I sent you?

01:10:34.814 --> 01:10:36.523
Yeah, I did. Thanks.

01:10:37.400 --> 01:10:39.192
I really want to see you.

01:10:40.528 --> 01:10:42.321
I don't know, Lisa.

01:10:42.488 --> 01:10:44.114
Let me think about it.

01:10:47.744 --> 01:10:49.786
Ladies and gentlemen,
please take your seats.

01:10:49.871 --> 01:10:53.040
The premiere ofJesus Christ
Superstar is about to begin.

01:10:53.124 --> 01:10:55.417
Hey, Reuby Tuesday!

01:10:56.544 --> 01:10:58.211
- Â¿CÃ³mo estÃ¡s?
- What are you doing here?

01:10:58.296 --> 01:11:01.214
What else? Hector's playing
keyboards in the band.

01:11:01.299 --> 01:11:03.342
I didn't figure you a fan
of musical theatre.

01:11:03.426 --> 01:11:06.094
My friend Sandy Lyle is in the show.

01:11:06.471 --> 01:11:08.931
Have you talked to Polly?

01:11:09.891 --> 01:11:13.185
She was upset, bro.
It must've been some kind of fight.

01:11:13.269 --> 01:11:16.146
Yeah, I keep calling her
and she won't pick up the phone.

01:11:16.230 --> 01:11:19.733
I don't know, I was thinking about
maybe dropping by tomorrow.

01:11:19.817 --> 01:11:23.320
It's a bit too late, papi.
She's leaving town in two hours.

01:11:23.738 --> 01:11:24.947
What?

01:11:25.907 --> 01:11:26.990
Why? Where is she going?

01:11:27.075 --> 01:11:29.618
I don't know. She said goodbye.
That's it.

01:11:29.911 --> 01:11:33.080
- Hi, I'm sorry I'm late.
- No, yeah. Hi.

01:11:35.041 --> 01:11:39.086
Hey, Javi, this is Lisa, my wife.

01:11:57.981 --> 01:12:02.025
Her mother told me she was back.
You're doing the right thing here.

01:12:02.110 --> 01:12:05.696
- Relax. I'm not promising anything.
- It's very exciting.

01:12:12.328 --> 01:12:13.912
Reuben, Stan. Change of plan.

01:12:13.997 --> 01:12:17.416
The meeting with Van Lew's board
and AFLAC has moved to 4:00.

01:12:17.500 --> 01:12:19.167
4:00? I don't know if I can do that.

01:12:19.252 --> 01:12:21.878
What's wrong with you?
Get your ass over here!

01:12:21.963 --> 01:12:24.506
Good evening, folks.
I'm Sandy Lyle

01:12:24.590 --> 01:12:27.092
and I've got
a very special announcement.

01:12:27.385 --> 01:12:29.302
Please note
that in tonight's performance,

01:12:29.387 --> 01:12:33.348
in addition to playing Judas,
I'll be playing Jesus as well.

01:12:33.433 --> 01:12:35.684
Thank you and enjoy the show.

01:12:35.768 --> 01:12:38.228
Sandy, what are you doing?
Wonsuk is playing Jesus.

01:12:38.312 --> 01:12:41.023
It's cool. I'll play dual roles.
Give me the crown, Wonsuk.

01:12:41.107 --> 01:12:43.150
Screwyou, Sandy,
you're a has-been.

01:12:43.234 --> 01:12:45.610
No one even cares
you were in that stupid movie.

01:12:45.695 --> 01:12:47.279
- Oh, no.
- Oh, shit!

01:12:50.324 --> 01:12:51.742
Judas is biting me!

01:12:54.412 --> 01:12:55.787
What happened in there?

01:12:55.872 --> 01:12:59.958
I'm a professional and I won't put
my reputation on the line

01:13:00.043 --> 01:13:02.085
for a group of freaking amateurs.

01:13:02.170 --> 01:13:05.380
It's always the same story
with you, pal.

01:13:07.550 --> 01:13:10.552
You did this one movie
a hundred years ago.

01:13:10.928 --> 01:13:14.473
From then on, you thought you were
better than everybody else.

01:13:14.932 --> 01:13:17.601
Why don't you let go,
move on with your life?

01:13:18.603 --> 01:13:20.729
It's not about
what happened in the past

01:13:20.813 --> 01:13:22.939
or what you think
might happen in the future.

01:13:23.024 --> 01:13:25.525
It's about the ride,
for Christ's sake.

01:13:26.652 --> 01:13:29.237
There's no point in going through
all this crap

01:13:29.322 --> 01:13:31.239
if you don't enjoy the ride.

01:13:31.532 --> 01:13:32.699
And you know what?

01:13:32.784 --> 01:13:36.286
When you least expect it,
something great might come along.

01:13:36.370 --> 01:13:38.955
Something better than
you even planned for.

01:13:41.959 --> 01:13:45.045
You were funny as hell
playing those bagpipes, though.

01:13:45.546 --> 01:13:47.714
Did I ever tell you that?

01:13:48.549 --> 01:13:51.927
I don't think I've ever heard you
speak before, Mr. Feffer.

01:13:57.934 --> 01:14:02.312
So, Reuby, are we going to grab
a bite after your work thingamajigy?

01:14:03.106 --> 01:14:04.731
No, Lisa...

01:14:05.817 --> 01:14:08.485
I shouldn't have asked you
to come down here.

01:14:08.736 --> 01:14:11.113
I'm not getting back together
with you.

01:14:11.864 --> 01:14:13.824
What are you talking about?

01:14:13.991 --> 01:14:15.534
- Why?
- "Why?"

01:14:17.745 --> 01:14:20.872
You screwed a scuba-diving
instructor on our honeymoon.

01:14:21.541 --> 01:14:26.002
What kind of cold, heartless bitch
would do that to someone they love?

01:14:27.130 --> 01:14:30.924
I'd have to be an idiot to get back
together with you after that.

01:14:31.884 --> 01:14:35.220
